<ce:para>Before hydrogen can find widespread use as a fuel, significant challenges associated with producing and reversibly storing hydrogen must be overcome. First principles calculations were used to screen candidate materials for hydrogen separation using metal alloy membranes and for reversible hydrogen storage using destabilized metal alloys. Calculation results identified important topics for continuing theoretical and experimental efforts. This is an abstract of a paper presented at the AIChE Annual Meeting (San Francisco, CA 11/12-17/2006).</ce:para>
